<p>

Welcome to the Claremont Institute Editorials page. The Claremont Institute frequently 
publishes articles of importance to California and the nation. Bookmark this page if you 
want to keep up with the Claremont Institute's positions on the important political and public policy issues of the day.

<P>

<hr noshade>

<P>

<DL>

<dt>

   <IMG ALIGN=left SRC  = "images/button.gif" HSPACE=5 vspace=5>

   <img src="images/new.gif" align="right">

<a href="edit/inaug97.htm"><b>Clinton's Craft and Republican Drift</b></a>

<dd>
-- By Charles L. Heatherly

<P>
<I> Where will all this newly acquired coolness leave the Republicans after the dust settles and the Clinton-Gore administration claims credit for whatever compromise legislation is eventually enacted? Do such pale "victories" provide the building blocks for expanding their majority in the 1998 congressional elections? Do they tell the citizens of the nation how a Republican government would differ from the status quo? Will such a me-too strategy give Republicans a platform for recapturing the White House in the year 2000?
These are the questions conservatives are asking themselves these days. </I>
<p>
<br clear=all>

<dt>

   <IMG ALIGN=left SRC  = "images/button.gif" HSPACE=5 vspace=5>

   <img src="images/new.gif" align="right">

<a href="edit/phonic.htm"><b>Phonics Triumphant? Traditional Reading Gets a Big Boost</b></a>

<dd>
-- By Ben Boychuk

<P>
<I> Gettysburg was one battle that changed a war. In December, education 
reformers, parents and everyday citizens who support phonics won such a 
fight in Sacramento. The outcome of a vote by the California Board of 
Education signals a decisive change in how public school children will be 
taught to read -- not just in the Golden State, but nationwide. </I>
<p>
<br clear=all>

<dt>

   <IMG ALIGN=left SRC  = "images/button.gif" HSPACE=5 vspace=5>


<a href="edit/jaffa.htm"><b>The Party of Lincoln vs. The Party of Bureaucrats</b></a>

<dd>
-- By Harry V. Jaffa

<P>
<I>In their convention acceptance speeches, both Bob Dole and Jack Kemp declared that the Republican Party is the party of Abraham Lincoln. But just what is the connection between the Republican Party of 1860 and 1996?</I>
<p>
<br clear=all>

<dt>

   <IMG ALIGN=left SRC  = "images/button.gif" HSPACE=5 vspace=5>

<a href="edit/2budgets.htm"><b>A Tale of Two Budgets</b></a>

<dd>
-- By Tom McClintock

<P>
<I>The old parable of the ant who stores a surplus in the summer to endure the winter is as true for governments as it is for families and businesses.</I>
<p>
<br clear=all>


<dt>

   <IMG ALIGN=left SRC  = "images/button.gif" HSPACE=5 vspace=5>

<a href="edit/mcclint.htm"><b>The High Cost of Racial and Gender Preferences</b></a>

<dd>
-- By Tom McClintock

<P>
<I>Racial and gender quotas now permeate virtually every aspect of California's government. These laws cost California taxpayers and consumers at least $343 million annually.</I>
<p>
<br clear=all>

<dt>

   <IMG ALIGN=left SRC  = "images/button.gif" HSPACE=5 vspace=5>

<a href="edit/marshal2.htm"><b>Diversity is Good--Discrimination Isn't</b></a>

<dd>
-- By Paul Marshall

<P>
<I> Corporations, universities, media and politicians gain little from the self-imposed sameness or "diversity".</I>
<p>
<br clear=all>


<dt>

   <IMG ALIGN=left SRC  = "images/button.gif" HSPACE=5 vspace=5>


<a href="edit/hersch2.htm"><b>Don't Look for the Terrorists</b></a>

<dd>
-- By Bruce Herschensohn

<P>
<I> Bringing terrorists "to justice" in the bombing of the U.S. base in Saudi Arabia is not enough. It's time for a real war on the Nation of Terrorism.</I>
<p>
<br clear=all>


<dt>

   <IMG ALIGN=left SRC  = "images/button.gif" HSPACE=5 vspace=5>

