<P>
<br>
<P>
While most sites on the World Wide Web request support of $25, $50 or more, the Frontiers of Freedom Institute would like to spend some quality months building our reputation and earning your respect.

<P><b>Therefore, we are asking for $1.  One dollar.</b>  It may not sound like a great deal of money to you, but frankly, thousands of web users log on to our site every week.  If everyone who viewed our site sent us $1, then we could continue producing quality conservative studies, conferences, and op-eds.  Of course, not everyone will send us $1.  However, we can only hope that this material is of concern enough for many people to simply slip a one dollar bill in an envelope and send it to us.  We will put it to constructive use.  It will allow us to continue moving the ball forward in the debate of conservative and limited government principles versus liberal big government dogma.
<P>
Certainly, if our op-eds and mission statement speak to you in a more passionate and personal way, we encourage you to think about a more substantial gift.
<P><blockquote><I>
For now, however, your support of $1 makes the philosophical connection between our organization and you.  It is a symbolic way of saying -- "Youre doing well.  Continue the fight."</blockquote></I><P>

We thank you for viewing our site and hope we can become more substantive partners in the future in order to advance conservative principles across the country.<P>

Please send your contribution to:<P>
<b><center>
The Honorable Malcolm Wallop<br>
Chairman<br>
Frontiers of Freedom Institute<br>
1735 North Lynn Street Suite 1050<br>
Arlington, Virginia   22209</b><br>
</center>
</b><p>
If you plan to send a check, please make the check out to Frontiers of Freedom Institute.<P>

The Frontiers of Freedom Institute is a 501(c)(3) non-profit educational and research organization which promotes a limited government, pro-growth agenda and specifically supports Constitutional freedoms such as the preservation of property rights, the sanctity of civil liberties, a strong national defense, and the privatization of Social Security.<P>

The Frontiers of Freedom Institutes main mission is to develop scientific studies, opinion papers, and in-depth research to support our stated issues.<P>

Contributions to the Frontiers of Freedom Institute are tax deductible and therefore the Institute cannot advocate legislative action or take part in the political process -- it is purely a research organization.<P>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
