<HEAD>
<TITLE>FREE Job Announcement</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" BACKGROUND="/free/Images/bluewhite_paper.gif"><IMG SRC = "/free/Images/flogo.gif" ALT = ""><H1><CENTER>Job Opportunity</CENTER></H1>
<P><H2><CENTER>Research Assistant
</CENTER></H2>

<P>
The Foundation for Research on Economics and the Environment (FREE) and the Gallatin Institute invites applications for the position of <B>Research Assistant</B>.  Duties, responsibilities, expectations, and compensation are equivalent to a master's level research assistantship.  Length of appointment is negotiable, but generally ranges from 21-24 months.  Our RAs normally move on to advanced graduate programs at top schools.<BR Clear=All>

<P>Primary responsibilities include: 
<OL><LI>researching, writing, and editing all public policy material of FREE and Gallatin Institute; 
<LI>assisting Chairman in composing and publishing material, especially bi-weekly <I>Seattle Times</I> op-eds, and also books, speeches, invited chapters, and other opinion pieces; and 
<LI>researching, writing, and editing other administrative documents, such as correspondences and grant proposals.</OL>  For consideration please send resume by <B>March 15</B> to <BR>
<CENTER>Christy Fullen-Operations Director<BR>
945 Technology Blvd., Suite 101F<BR>
Bozeman, MT 59715</CENTER><P>
 More information is available on our home pages: <A HREF="http://www.free-eco.org">http://www.free-eco.org</A> and <A HREF="http://www.gallatin.org/gallatin">http://www.gallatin.org</A>.
<H3><CENTER>Job Description</CENTER></H3>
<DL><DT><B>Research</B>:  
<DD>keep abreast of all relevant current events and scholarly research on topics relevant to FREE and Gallatin Institute's missions.
<DT><B>Public outreach</B>:  
<DD>respond to requests for information and research from the public.  This requires familiarity and organization of FREE and Gallatin Institute's files and archives, electronic and hardcopy.
<DT><B>Computer Systems Administrator</B>:  
<DD>troubleshoot all bugs, install and maintain updated and functional software, hardware, and networking on all office and home computers, provide training for all employees as to the operation of computers, and implement new fixes and features to office computers as appropriate.
<DT><B>Webmaster</B>:  
<DD>serve as online coordinator for FREE and Gallatin Institute.  Answer all e-mail; create and maintain websites for both organizations; troubleshoot and debug online resources; maintain vendor relations for technical aspects; maintain relations with publishers, writers, and other business contacts via modem; keep websites up-to-date with current FREE and Gallatin publications; provide for future online resource development for FREE and Gallatin (including distribution lists, listservs, chat rooms etc.); and promote FREE and Gallatin's online presence.
<DT><B>Conference Support</B>:  
<DD>during FREE and Gallatin Institute's conferences, attend in an official capacity and support Conference Coordinator, Chairman, and participants.  This includes chauffeuring, running errands, setting up equipment, socializing with attendees, etc.  Take notes on proceedings for future use in other duties.
<DT><B>Office duties</B>: 
<DD>answering phones, meeting visitors, processing mail, attending meetings, adhering to dress code, hold normal business hours (8am to 5pm, plus other hours as required), filing, and general administrative work.
<DT><B>Attend Conferences </B>
<DD>relevant to research and public outreach duties.</DL>


<P><H4>Expectations:</H4>  
<UL><LI>60-plus hour work week
<LI>Congenial attitude
<LI>Totally reliable</UL>

<H3><CENTER>Work Environment</CENTER></H3>

<P>
FREE and Gallatin are 501(c)(3) research and education foundations, based in Bozeman, Montana, a town of 27,000.  Both organizations are under the direction of <A HREF="/free/john.html">John Baden, Ph.D.</A> and are administered by a full-time <A HREF="/free/FREE.staff.html">staff</A> of four.  
</P>
<P>
FREE conducts environmental economics and public policy seminars for academics, columnists and editors, environmental writers and federal judges.  FREE illustrates how science and economic analysis can help make responsible decisions.
</P>
<P>
The Gallatin Institute links essayists, poets, and novelists with economists and policy analysts interested in rural areas and communities in the West.  Gallatin believes that writers are best equipped to engage in and inspire a constructive, honest debate about the West's present and future.
</P>
<P>
The work environment is close knit, friendly, flexible and productive.  The nature of our works requires efficiency and professionalism.  Business dress code is required.  All employees are hired on a probationary status for ninety days.  We strongly support efforts that contribute to our employees' physical and emotional health.  We contribute towards employees' health care plans and are supportive of time off for family and personal matters.  We encourage athletic membership at a local gym.  Vacation time is not fixed; it generally follows the holiday schedule of <A HREF="http://www.montana.edu">Montana State University</A> and is negotiated on a case by case basis.
</P>

<P>

<!--FOOT--><HR>
