<HTML>   
<HEAD>   
<TITLE>League Philosophy</TITLE>   
</HEAD>   
<BODY>   
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#2F4F2F" vlink="#3232CD">   
<img src="/savers/images/tnygrngr.gif" alt=" "><FONT size=5><b><a 
name="phil">League Philosophy</a></b></FONT><BR>
<img src="/savers/images/smgrnln1.gif"> 
<br>
<P>   
<center><b><i>All of your savings and investments should be tax deductible and tax   
deferred<br>  
until you, or your beneficiary, consume it.</i></b></center><br>  
<p>  
The Savers &amp; Investors League was organized in 1988 by <a   
href="/savers/library/tkbio.html">Tom Kelly</a> who recognized the compelling,   
critical need for increased personal savings and investment to foster healthy economic growth in the    
United States. <br>   
<p>   
Without question, private savings and investment is the  foundation for increased personal and national     
prosperity.  Whether these savings are in bank accounts, stocks, bonds, CDs, IRAs, insurance, annuities,    
pension funds, mutual funds, etc., they constitute the vital capital base needed and utilized by individuals,    
families, businesses, and government.<BR>   
<p>   
 On a personal level, insufficient savings creates uncertainty for future retirement, as well as uncertainty   
as to the family financial resources of home and health care needs and desires.  A diminished supply of    
private capital on a national scale causes interest rates to rise and economic growth to slow. Also,    
wages,jobs, and standards-of-living suffer.<br><br>   
 Disastrously, the government continues to pass or maintain self-defeating, senseless laws that   
limit and penalize tax-deferred savings plans such as IRA's, 401(k) s and pensions.<BR>   
<p>   
The annual income tax imposed upon investment return and   
realized gain needlessly and scandalously decreases  the country's   
vital capital base year after year. Not only do taxpayers suffer,   
the government's tax base is progressively reduced too.<BR>   
<P>   
The Nation must maximize personal savings and investment,   
so that private capital will grow and expand as quickly, and as   
soundly, as possible.<BR>   
<P>   
The Individual Investment Account, Senate Bill  
 <a href="/savers/legislation/s159.html">S. 159</a> and House Bill  
 <a href="/savers/legislation/hr328.html">H.R. 328</a>, accomplishes   
this simple but vital objective.<br>  
<p>  
The League helped develop this legislation and works diligently to secure its   
enactment.  The bipartisan sponsors are: Senator John Breaux</a>, Democrat,  
 Senate Finance Committee, and Representative Jim McCrery, Republican,  
 House Ways &amp; Means Committee.<br>  
<p>  
This simple, straight-forward legislation creates IRA-type accounts that provide -   
<br>  
<ul>  
<li>Unlimited, tax-deductible contributions for everyone<br><br>  
<li>No penalty taxes on any account withdrawal<br><br>  
<li>No forced distributions at any time<br><br>  
<li>No income tax nor estate tax at death<br><br>  
<li>Account holder, or beneficiary, only pay taxes on account withdrawals<br><br>  
</ul>  
<p>  
The Individual Investment Account Act has been described by leading tax economists   
as <i>&quot;one of the boldest, most imaginative, and most constructive pro-growth   
tax initiatives in many years.&quot;</i>  
<p>  
<hr>   
 [<a href="/savers/">Home</a>]  
 </BODY>   
   
</HTML>   
  

