<HTML>    
<HEAD>    
<TITLE>League Structure and Support</TITLE>    
</HEAD>    
<BODY>    
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#2F4F2F" vlink="#3232CD">    
<img src="/savers/images/tnygrngr.gif" alt=" ">
<FONT size=5><b><a name="sands">League Structure and 
Support</a></b></FONT><BR>   
<img src="/savers/images/smgrnln1.gif"> <br> 
<P>    
Because the League lobbies Congress on behalf of voter/taxpayers,
 it is a 501(c)(4) non profit corporation.     
Therefore, contributions to the League are not deductible as charitable contributions for Federal income     
tax purposes. However, contributions to the League may be deductible as an ordinary and necessary     
business expense, or an expense incurred in the production of income.<BR>    
<p> The League's affiliated Savers &amp; Investors Foundation carries out research endeavors that     
explore the impact of taxes on our economy, as well as on taxpayers, our government, and our nation. The     
Foundation is a 501(c)(3) research and educational nonprofit organization. 
Contributions to it are tax     deductible.    
<BR>    
<P>    
Neither the League nor the Foundation have a minimum or    
maximum contribution limit. All contributors choose the contribution    
amount most suitable for themselves.<b> While voluntary contributions    
from all sources are vital to the League's and Foundation's work,    
each voter/taxpayer's active participation via on-going communications    
with his or her Senators and Representative, regardless of contribution    
level, is what really counts. </b> Members of Congress respond to    
strong constituent interest. As a result of the League's activities, 
savers and investors become an increasingly powerful, focused force 
before Congress and the Administration.<BR>    
<p>    
<hr>
[<a href="/savers/">Home</a>], [<a href="/savers/member.html">Membership 
Information</a>]   
 </BODY>    
    
</HTML>    
   

