</DOCHDR>
<html>
<head><title>League Membership Information</title></head>
<body>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#2F4F2F" vlink="#3232CD">
<center><img src ="/savers/images/griffgrn.gif" alt=" "><br>
<img src="/savers/images/boxloggr.gif" alt="Savers &amp; Investors League"><br>
<hr>
<font size=6><b><i>Membership Information</i></b></font></center>
<hr>
<p><br>
The Savers &amp; Investors League is a nonpartisan, nonprofit 
501(c)(4) grass-roots lobbying organization.  Its purpose is to promote 
private saving and 
investment to foster healthy economic growth in the United States.  To
this end, the League develops sound legislative proposals, as well as
circulates information relating to existing and proposed legislation 
which it believes has either a positive or negative effect on saving 
and investing.  It intends to affect such legislation through grass
roots and direct lobbying efforts.<br>
<p>
The League is committed to action-oriented, legislative projects.
Every effort is made to distribute its views and proposals to Congress, 
the Administration, and other policy and opinion leaders nationally and 
locally to ensure that they are widely examined and discussed.  The 
League also disseminates its view via an active media and Internet 
program.<br>
<p>
Every voter/taxpayer (regardless of age or tax bracket) who saves and 
invests has a vital, personal interest in removing the severe income tax 
bias against saving and investing.  As we all know, Congress and the 
Administration pay close attention to public pressure.  Thus, <i>your</i>
 membership is most important because you join with many others to create 
and build the powerful political force so badly needed for success.<br>
<p>
While the Savers &amp; Investors League does not require any kind of annual 
fee to initiate or maintain membership, it does rely on 
voluntary contributions 
from individuals and corporations for its support.<br>
<p>
Because the League lobbies on your behalf, contributions paid to the League 
are not deductible 
as charitable contributions for Federal income tax purposes.  However, 
such contributions may be deductible as an ordinary and necessary 
business expense, or an expense incurred in the production of income to 
the extent permitted by law.<br>
<hr>
<p>
<I>
If you would like to join us in this vital, positive campaign to remove 
the tax bias against saving, you can either fill out our <a href="/savers/guestbook.html">On-Line Membership Form</a>, <a href="https://secure.townhall.com/savers/savers-sec.html">Secure On-Line Membership Form</a>, or print out the <a href="/savers/form.html">Hard Copy Form</a> 
and mail it to:</I><br> 
<p>
<center><b>Savers &amp; Investors League<br>
P.O. Box 279<br>
Wayne, PA  19087<br></b></center><p>
<I>

If you would like more information about the League, you can  
contact us via:</I><br>
<p>
<center>
<b>
Phone:</b> 1-800-527-2365<br>
<b>Fax:</b> 610/989-3972, or<br>
<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto:savers@savers.org">savers@savers.org</a><br>
</center>
<p>
<hr>
[<a href="/savers/">Home</a>]<br>
<font size=2>Savers &amp; Investors League, January 1997</font>
</body></html>

