<html>

<title>Daily Commentary - January 14, 1997</title>

<body>

<center><h1>Daily Commentary<br>
January 14, 1997</h1></center>

<p><hr width=75% size=3><p>

I'm Gary Bauer for Washington Watch.

<p>

Have you ever noticed how America's elites always assume it's
inevitable that our young people are increasingly liberal in their
values?  Well there's a new survey out that shows the elites are
wrong once again.

<p>

The Higher Education Research Institute's survey of over 250,000
college freshmen shows that students are actually becoming --
listen to this -- more conservative.  For the fourth year in a
row, the number of students who support legalized abortion has
declined.  And there's no &quot;gender gap&quot; on the question.

<p>

The survey also showed that support for casual sex has reached
an all-time low. Over half of students now say that promiscuity should 
be avoided. They also say criminals should be punished, not coddled. 
Today's young people are also more self-confident and civic-minded, with
record numbers performing volunteer work and community service.  And 
up to 30 percent identify themselves as &quot;Born Again Christians.&quot;

<p>

These are exciting trends.  They show that conservatism is borne
out in practical experience.  It looks like increasingly young 
Americans are concluding that liberalism is a dead end.

<p>

For Family Research Council, this is Gary Bauer with today's
Washington Watch.  For more information about us, call 1-800-225-4008.
That number again:  1-800-225-4008.

<p>

<center><b>
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/wwold.html.cgi#current">Last Month's Commentaries</a>] 
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/wwdaily.html.cgi#current">This Month's Commentaries</a>]
</b></center>

<p>

<HR SIZE = 3>

<p>

